= Sprint Meeting Minutes (Product Owner)

Sprint window: Feb 9–Feb 21, 2026  \
Product: Noru

== Meeting 1 — Feb 9, 2026
- Objective: Align on MVP scope and outcomes.
- Decision: University sign-in is mandatory.
- Decision: Onboarding photo is mandatory before ride access.
- Decision: Keep initial release simple and mobile-first.
- Action: Prioritize trust-first onboarding over additional features.

== Meeting 2 — Feb 11, 2026
- Objective: Confirm product approach and sprint boundaries.
- Decision: Keep a single clear user journey for this sprint.
- Decision: Avoid adding non-essential experiences.
- Scope change: De-prioritize web-facing extras.
- Action: Approve focused delivery plan for onboarding and core ride flow.

== Meeting 3 — Feb 13, 2026
- Objective: Mid-sprint progress review.
- Outcome: Onboarding path is usable but needs stability improvements.
- Decision: Keep UX minimal and reduce optional complexity.
- Risk: Sign-in and onboarding reliability can affect completion.
- Action: Maintain completion reliability as release gate.

== Meeting 4 — Feb 16, 2026
- Objective: Blocker review and scope protection.
- Decision: Prioritize stability work before adding new scope.
- Decision: Keep current product direction unchanged.
- Risk: Inconsistent onboarding completion impacts pilot confidence.
- Action: Hold back non-critical enhancements.

== Meeting 5 — Feb 19, 2026
- Objective: Expand to core ride value after stability gains.
- Decision: Include create, browse, join, and stop ride lifecycle.
- Decision: Keep host and joinee journeys distinct.
- Decision: Default completed users to pick/join rides.
- Action: Approve visual polish without adding UX complexity.

== Meeting 6 — Feb 21, 2026
- Objective: Sprint closeout and artifact readiness.
- Decision: Keep native back behavior and clear host flow.
- Decision: Include quick destination and source/destination swap in host flow.
- Decision: Keep payments peer-to-peer outside the app.
- Deliverable: Finalize diagrams and user-flow documentation.
- Next focus: Pilot hardening, trust operations, and fare guidance details.
